<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor Bradley is out and Police Chief Darryl Gates is in for a cameo part in an 
upcoming "Hunter" segment on NBC. With Bradley involved in the mayoral 
campaign, his appearance would necessitate equal time for other candidates. 
Though Gates has already filmed the role, NBC faces a similar equal time 
situation should he decide to run for governor. The role: a police chief 
delivering a message about cracking down on crime. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
