<HEADLINE>
<P>
REWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After reading Sherry Potter's letter ("Reward", Jan.5) concerning lost wallets 
and rewards, I'd like to describe my own recent experience. While on jury duty 
in Glendale in December, I visited the main Pasadena City Library and found a 
wallet (filled with driver's license and other valuable cards) in the parking 
lot. 
</P>
<P>
I drove over to the owner's address and left a note with my name and telephone 
under his door. When I returned to my parked car, I discovered a $20 parking 
ticket on my windshield. I drove over to Pasadena City Hall and paid the 
ticket. Two days later, the owner of the wallet telephoned and I mailed the 
lost wallet back to his Pasadena address. Lo and behold, the owner( Michael 
Ackley) sent a letter of thanks and enclosed a $25 check to cover the $20 
parking ticket and my expenses. 
</P>
<P>
KENNETH LLOYD LARSON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
