<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
POLICEMAN WOUNDS SUSPECTED ROBBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beverly Hills police shot and wounded a suspected robber Tuesday after he 
allegedly advanced toward a detective while wielding a knife, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Julio Quilla, 30, was in serious but stable condition at a Beverly Hills 
hospital after being shot once in the stomach, Lt. Dave Griffey said. 
</P>
<P>
An unidentified officer received a superficial wound when the bullet ricocheted 
from the suspect and struck the officer's leg, Griffey said. 
</P>
<P>
Quilla entered an elevator with a woman in an office building at 333 S. Beverly 
Drive, Griffey said. The woman later told officers that Quilla threatened her 
with a knife and attempted to rob her. She began screaming, officers said, and 
the suspect ran without taking anything when the elevator doors opened. 
</P>
<P>
Plainclothes officers later saw a man running and carrying a knife near a 
supermarket at Beverly Drive and Olympic Boulevard, police said. The officers 
ordered the man to stop, but he "started running right at our detectives with a 
knife," Griffey said. An officer who was not identified fired one shot, 
wounding Quilla, police said. He will be booked on suspicion of robbery and 
assault with a deadly weapon, Griffey said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
