her, was ordered held on $500,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
Lee is charged with attempted murder, child endangerment, inflicting corporal 
punishment on a child and assault with a deadly weapon. She appeared before San 
Diego Municipal Judge H. Ronald Domnitz in chains and jail clothing. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Aaron Katz unsuccessfully argued that bail should be set at 
$1 million. Katz declined to say how many stab wounds the boy suffered and did 
not divulge the child's name to reporters. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't want to go into details of the case. The police are still 
investigating. . . . She's had mental problems in the past," Katz said. 
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor did say that Lee tried to buy a gun last month, but did not want 
to wait for the 15-day waiting period that is required for such purchases. 
</P>
<P>
The boy remains hospitalized with wounds suffered in the attack Saturday at the 
family home. 
</P>
<P>
Lee and her husband also have a 13-year-old daughter. 
</P>
<P>
Domnitz set a March 3 preliminary hearing. 
