<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAVES PLAY HOST TO SANTA CLARA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RAY RIPTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pepperdine, which has lost 4 of its last 5 basketball games, will open West 
Coast Athletic Conference play at home this week, playing host to Santa Clara 
at 8 tonight and to the University of San Francisco at 7:30 Thursday at 
Firestone Fieldhouse in Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara (11-2) has won 6 in a row and is off to its best start since 
opening with 12 wins and 2 losses in the 1977-78 season. The Broncos' only 
losses have been at Indiana, 64-49, and at UC Santa Barbara, 64-57. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara senior forward Jens Gordon, who is averaging team-high marks of 
16.5 points and 9.4 rebounds a game, is one of 5 Broncos scoring in double 
figures. 
</P>
<P>
The Broncos are coming off a 53-51 win at Boise State last Saturday. 
Pepperdine's last game was also against Boise State, a 63-60 overtime loss at 
home last Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Junior forward Dexter Howard, who is averaging 18.6 points and 8.2 rebounds, 
leads the Waves (8-7). RAY RIPTON 
