<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The former law partner of ex-Rep. Mario Biaggi was sentenced to six years in 
prison and fined $222,000 for his role in the Wedtech racketeering case. 
Bernard Ehrlich, 59, who was found guilty of 11 counts of racketeering, 
conspiracy, extortion and bribery, remains free on bail pending appeal. He was 
convicted last summer with Biaggi and three other people of turning the Wedtech 
Corp., the now-defunct South Bronx military contractor, into a racketeering 
enterprise for their personal gain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
