THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Francisco police officers used a steel battering ram to smash into an 
apartment where they interrupted an alleged drug deal and set off a shoot-out 
in which two suspects were wounded. Capt. Michael Brush said one group of 
suspects was being ripped off by another group just as the officers entered to 
serve a drug warrant. The suspects reportedly began shooting and the officers 
returned fire. One man was wounded in the knee and another was grazed in the 
head. Nine people were arrested. Officers said they confiscated a large bag 
containing what appeared to be cocaine as well as weapons and ammunition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
