<P>
MISSILE IN MOCK ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By UPI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Navy Tomahawk cruise missile was launched Tuesday from a submarine submerged 
off the coast of Maine and flew a mock land attack to a naval reservation near 
Rangely, the Pentagon announced. The missile is intended to provide the Navy 
with an all-weather option to manned aircraft strikes against heavily defended 
targets. 
