<TEXT>
<P>
A delivery worker pumped 58 gallons of fuel oil into a home converted to gas 
heat, causing an explosion and fire that destroyed two homes and hospitalized 
one woman, authorities said Tuesday. Police said the unidentified worker 
apparently stopped at the wrong address Monday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MISTAKES; EXPLOSIONS -- PENNSYLVANIA; DELIVERY WORKERS; NATURAL GAS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
