<P>
ASTROS GET RHODEN FOR 3 MINOR LEAGUERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New York Yankees traded right-hander Rick Rhoden Tuesday to the Houston 
Astros for three minor leaguers. 
</P>
<P>
Going to the Yankees were outfielder John Fishel, right-hander Pedro DeLeon and 
left-hander Mike Hook. 
</P>
<P>
Rhoden, 35, had a 12-12 record and a 4.20 earned-run average in 30 starts with 
the Yankees last season. 
</P>
<P>
Fishel, who had 18 home runs for triple-A Tucson last season, has been assigned 
to the Yankees' 40-player roster. DeLeon and Hook have been assigned to the 
Yankees' double-A Albany roster. 
</P>
