</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jurors chosen for the drunk-driving manslaughter trial of Olympic diver Bruce 
Kimball included a man whose daughter is a president of Students Against Drunk 
Drivers. 
</P>
<P>
Four men and two women plus an alternate were picked after 2 days of intense 
questioning, thus precluding having to move proceedings because of excessive 
publicity. Opening statements were set to begin today at Tampa, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
The last of the six jurors chosen, William Sherman, a postal worker and former 
Air Force sergeant, told attorneys that his daughter was chapter president of 
SADD at her high school in Brandon, a Tampa suburb where the fatal accident 
occurred last Aug. 1. 
</P>
<P>
Kimball is charged with driving a sports car through a group of teen-agers at a 
roadside hangout in an accident in which two teens were killed and four others 
were injured. 
