<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BOYS' BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
STRONG FINISH ENABLES BELL-JEFF TO NOTCH 14TH VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Powered by Nick Sanderson's 29 points and Greg Dunn's 20, Bell-Jeff High rolled 
to an 84-65 victory over St. Genevieve in a San Fernando Valley League game at 
Harvard on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Despite the win, however, Bell-Jeff Coach Joe Dunn was not pleased with the 
play of the Guards (14-1, 2-0 in league play). 
</P>
<P>
"We've yet to put together four good quarters this season," Dunn said. "I know 
it sounds funny to hear a coach complain when he's 14-1, but I'm always looking 
ahead. Sooner or later, we're going to run into a team that plays well for four 
quarters." 
</P>
<P>
With guard Chris Dyer getting into early foul trouble, Bell-Jeff struggled in 
the first half. 
</P>
<P>
The Guards trailed St. Genevieve, 24-18, midway through the second quarter 
before reeling off a 12-4 streak to end the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
In the second half, Bell-Jeff began to pick up the defensive intensity and it 
paid off in the fourth quarter when the Guards outscored the Valiants, 33-19. 
</P>
<P>
Sanderson scored 15 points in the final quarter and 21 points in the second 
half. Dyer scored 11 of his 13 points in final 2 periods. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Cassidy had 21 points and 10 assists for St. Genevieve (1-1 in league 
play). 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs 75, Alhambra 67 -- Trailing, 64-59, with 5 minutes to play, Burroughs 
went on a 16-3 tear to win the Foothill League game at Alhambra. 
</P>
<P>
Marnie Calderon's 3-point shot with 3:30 left gave the Indians a 66-65 lead 
they never relinquished. Calderon also had 8 assists. 
</P>
<P>
All-Foothill League forward Dan Murphy scored a game-high 25 points -- 10 in 
the fourth quarter -- and grabbed 14 rebounds for Burroughs (10-5, 2-0). 
Teammate Tom Clemons had 11 points and 9 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs made 12 of 15 free throws in the final period and 20 of 30 in the 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade 56, Harvard 45 -- Chris Bruckner scored 7 of his game-high 28 points 
in the fourth quarter and teammate Pete Miller scored 8 of his 12 in the fourth 
quarter as Chaminade pulled away in the San Fernando Valley league game at 
Chaminade. 
</P>
<P>
Leading, 41-38, at the end of the third quarter, Chaminade spread the court in 
the fourth period as Miller and Bruckner took charge, scoring all of the 
Eagles' points. 
</P>
<P>
Bruckner, a 6-5 senior forward, made 11 of 14 field-goal attempts and 6 of 7 
free throws and also had 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Miller added 7 assists for Chaminade (6-6, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Mike Beckwith scored 24 points for Harvard but was held to 2 points in the 
second half as Chaminade's Colin Havert hounded him after halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Teammate Rick Osterloh added 13 points for Harvard (0-2 in league play). 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 56, Calabasas 54 -- The Chargers outscored the Coyotes, 19-5, in the 
final period to come from behind in the Frontier league game at Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Fuller scored 12 points for Agoura (3-8, 1-1) and Tim Friedlander had a 
game-high 23 points for Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
Quartz Hill 72, Canyon 69 (OT) -- Shawn Klezovich scored off a turnover to send 
the game into overtime and then made 3 free throws in the extra period to hold 
off Canyon in the Golden League game. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon led by as many as 15 in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Hart 70, Burbank 64 -- Brett Wilson scored 12 of his game-high 27 points in the 
fourth quarter to lead Hart (8-7, 2-0) to the Foothill League victory. 
</P>
<P>
Wilson, playing in the low post, hit 10 of 17 field-goal attempts. Michael 
Ohlman scored 9 of his 14 points by hitting 3 of 4 from 3-point range. 
</P>
<P>
Burbank fell to 0-2 in league play and 2-12 overall. 
</P>
<P>
Montclair Prep 97, Marshall Fundamental 80 -- A second-quarter full-court press 
by Montclair Prep forced Marshall Fundamental into 6 turnovers, turning a 
6-point lead into a 16-point advantage. 
</P>
<P>
Montclair Prep also converted 36 of 48 free throws, many deriving from fast 
break fouls and fourth-quarter desperation fouls. 
</P>
<P>
J. T. Billingslea and James Gerber scored 25 and 26 points, respectively, for 
Montclair Prep. 
</P>
<P>
Village Christian 62, L.A. Baptist 56 -- Senior forward Mike Curl scored 11 
first-quarter points, leading Village Christian to a 10-point lead it never 
relinquished. 
</P>
<P>
Village Christian, took only 6 3-point shots, opting to take advantage of L. A. 
Baptist's sagging zone by pounding the ball inside. 
</P>
<P>
Buckley 45, Providence 38 -- Senior forward Todd Steinman scored a game-high 12 
points to lead Buckley (4-4, 1-0) in a Delphic League opener at Buckley. 
</P>
<P>
Grace Community 77, Newbridge 51 -- Grace Community (7-3, 2-0) received a total 
of 52 points from starting guards Scott Lechuga and Anthony Serra in the 
Westside League game. 
</P>
<P>
Highland Hall 73, Oak Hill 55 -- Robert Ramirez hit 6 3-point shots and scored 
25 points for the Hawks (6-3, 2-0) in the Westside League game at Highland 
Hall. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Smith scored 25 points for Oak Hill (5-4, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
L.A. Lutheran 52, Antelope Valley Christian 44 -- Junior forward Stephen 
Willweber had team-highs with 16 points and 13 rebounds to lead L. A. Lutheran 
to a nonleague win at home. 
</P>
<P>
West L.A. Baptist 61, West Valley Christian 60 -- Despite 27 points from 
sophomore center Chris McWhorter, West Valley Christian lost its second 
consecutive Westside League game by 1 point. 
</P>
</TEXT>
