<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BOYS' SOCCER; 
</P>
<P>
AGOURA ERUPTS IN SECOND HALF TO POST 8TH CONSECUTIVE VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Held scoreless in the first half, Agoura High exploded for 6 goals after 
intermission to defeat Santa Clara, 6-0, in a Frontier League boys' soccer 
match Tuesday at Santa Clara. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Friedman scored 2 goals and assisted Dominic Zapata on another as the 
Chargers (11-2-1, 2-0 in league play) won their eighth consecutive match. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura, the 1987 Southern Section 1-A Division champion and a semifinalist last 
year, is ranked No. 1 in this week's poll. 
</P>
<P>
St. Francis 2, Loyola 0 -- Led by All-American nominee Roberto Guerrero, St. 
Francis won a Del Rey League opener at St. Francis before 300 spectators. 
</P>
<P>
Guerrero and teammate Matt Hydar each scored second-half goals for the Golden 
Knights (9-1, 1-0), who are ranked No. 8 in the Southern Section 3-A Division. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade 2, Harvard 0 (OT) -- Seniors Nico Fasano and Brady Mitchell scored in 
overtime for Chaminade (6-2, 1-0) in a San Fernando Valley League match at 
Chaminade. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. Baptist 2, Village Christian 1 -- Shane Wight scored both goals, including 
the game-winner with 18 minutes remaining, to lead L. A. Baptist in an Alpha 
League match. 
</P>
<P>
L. A. Baptist (10-4, 2-0) is ranked No. 2 in the Southern Section Small Schools 
Division. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Jones scored for Village Christian (4-4-2, 0-2). 
</P>
<P>
In Monday's matches: 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando 3, Canoga Park 1 -- Elenilson Garcia, Jaime Ballesteros and Sergio 
Pizano all scored second-half goals to lead host San Fernando (4-2, 1-1) to a 
Northwest Valley Conference victory. 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 1, El Camino Real 0 -- Heros Daniels scored 14 minutes into the 
second half to lead Granada Hills (3-1-1, 1-1) to a Northwest Valley Conference 
win at home. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 0, Cleveland 0 -- Host Cleveland (2-3-1, 1-0-1) remained undefeated 
in Northwest Valley Conference play. 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley 2, Newbury Park 0 -- James Albin and Willie Ruiz scored second-half 
goals to lead the Pioneers in a Marmonte League match at Simi Valley. 
Goalkeeper Dan Madsen had 6 saves for Simi Valley (15-2, 3-0). 
</P>
<P>
Taft 6, Kennedy 0 -- Jake Gwin and Carlos Lopez each scored 2 goals for Taft 
(4-2) in a Northwest Valley Conference match at Kennedy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
