<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian's proposed state budget includes these Orange County 
projects: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 
</P>
<P>
Physical Sciences Building renovation: $10.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
Working drawings for a new science library: $1.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
Building the first phase in expansion of campus road system, including a new 
campus entrance on south side: $3.25 million. 
</P>
<P>
Preliminary plans to increase chilled water system to 6,500 tons: $135,000. 
</P>
<P>
Planning for a building to house engineering programs, the central computing 
facility and general classrooms: $975,000. 
</P>
<P>
UCI Medical Center 
</P>
<P>
Up to $8 million to compensate center for care provided to poor. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 
</P>
<P>
Equipment to complete an addition to Engineering Building: $2.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
Working drawings and building addition to McCarthy Hall science building: $22.4 
million. 
</P>
<P>
Planning classroom and faculty office building to accommodate 2,000 students, 
100 faculty offices and administrative space: $307,000. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago Community College 
</P>
<P>
Equipment for new classroom building: $552,000 
</P>
<P>
Working drawings for addition to Centennial Education Center to provide 
classroom, office and library space: $78,000. 
</P>
<P>
Chino Hills State Park 
</P>
<P>
Buying new lands for park: $10.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
Finishing construction of initial park facilities: $75,000. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans 
</P>
<P>
Addition of 47 engineers and other workers to oversee building county toll 
roads: $3.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
Amtrak 
</P>
<P>
Roadbed improvements on San Diegan rail service connecting Los Angeles with San 
Diego through the county: $10 million. 
</P>
<P>
Source: State Department of Finance 
</P>
