<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
9 IN VAN INJURED AS IT OVERTURNS AFTER COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nine people traveling in a Toyota van were injured Tuesday when the van 
collided with a Dodge Aries at a Huntington Beach intersection, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 10:20 a.m. when Sandra Greeley, 48, of Huntington 
Beach was traveling eastbound on Atlanta Avenue in her Dodge Aries and collided 
with the van driven by Christine Greasley, 36, who was traveling southbound on 
Beach Boulevard, Police Lt. Bill Mamelli said. 
</P>
<P>
"Greeley's vehicle struck the right side of Greasley's vehicle," he said. "The 
van went out of control, rolled over and ejected three of the nine occupants." 
</P>
<P>
The driver and all of the passengers in the van were injured. The driver of the 
Aries was not, Mamelli said. 
</P>
<P>
The most seriously injured were identified as Joan Greasley, 61, of 
Leicestershire, England, who suffered a concussion and a fractured skull; and 
Linda Tacey, 38, of Cornwall, England, who also suffered a concussion. They 
were in serious condition at Fountain Valley Regional Hospital &amp; Medical 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
The others who suffered minor injuries, including cuts and bruises, were 
identified as Christine Greasley, 36; Phil Greasley, 38; Michelle Tacey, 6, and 
Laura Greasley, 2, all of Huntington Beach; Derrick Greasley, 31, and Albert 
Greasley, 62, of Leicestershire, England; and Richard Handley, 50, of Cornwall, 
England. 
</P>
<P>
Neither driver was cited, but the accident remains under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
