<P>
GIRL'S BODY REJECTS BOY'S HEART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PATTERSON, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The heart of a 15-year-old boy -- transplanted into the girl he loved three 
years ago -- is being rejected by the girl's body, and she will have to undergo 
another transplant. 
</P>
<P>
Doctors are looking for a suitable heart for Donna Ashlock, 18, who has been 
living on the heart of Felipe Garza since Jan. 4, 1986. Doctors learned last 
month that the Garza heart has been permanently damaged by repeated attempts by 
Donna's body to reject it. Garza died of a broken blood vessel in his brain 
only a few days after he told his mother that he had had a premonition of death 
and that he wanted his heart to go to Donna, who had learned a year earlier 
that she needed a transplant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
