<P>
NAZI VICTIMS' REMAINS SEIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two West German universities have been ordered to stop using the remains of 
Nazi extermination victims -- some of them decapitated -- in medical education, 
a state government official said today. 
</P>
<P>
Chancellor Helmut Kohl expressed shock over the practice after Israel and the 
West German Jewish community urged him to ensure that the remains of Communists 
and mentally handicapped people murdered by the Nazis were removed. Christoph 
Keller, spokesman for the Baden-Wuerttemberg Science and Culture Ministry, said 
three tissue samples and 150 specimens from Nazi victims had been taken away 
from the prestigious universities of Heidelberg and Tuebingen. 
</P>
