IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FALCONS SAFETY HAS KNEE SURGERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SUWANEE, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Atlanta Falcons strong safety Robert Moore has undergone arthroscopic surgery 
on his right knee, the NFL club announced today. The Falcons said Moore, 24, 
injured the knee in the final game of the season against New Orleans. Team 
doctor John Garrett said Moore, who started all 16 games and had 117 tackles 
and five interceptions, is expected to be released from the hospital Thursday 
and will begin a six-month rehabilitation program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
