<HEADLINE>
<P>
BENGALS BAR REPORTERS FROM PRACTICE FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City police turned reporters away from the Cincinnati Bengals' practice complex 
today after the team, preparing to play Jan. 22 in the Super Bowl, abruptly 
canceled a scheduled news conference with coach Sam Wyche. 
</P>
<P>
Wyche decided to cancel the meeting with reporters because he needed the time 
to prepare for the Super Bowl game against the San Francisco 49ers, said Allan 
Heim, the Bengals' director of public relations. The Bengals had previously 
issued a media advisory to reporters in which the NFL team said Wyche would be 
available at specified times every day this week. 
</P>
<P>
Two police officers stopped reporters at the gate of the Bengals' Spinney Field 
training complex to say the facility was closed to the press. 
</P>
<P>
Wyche had already spent some time Monday and Tuesday with reporters and will be 
available to them Thursday and Friday, so he decided to cancel today's session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
